snippet.textDisplay: Trust me, the form factor of the new Xbox is necessary to deliver a generational leap in processing power at this time. This is because advancements in microprocessor architecture has stagnated (see Moore's law). They have to rely on increasing clock speeds, which requires more power and produces more heat. Hence the larger case for better cooling (like a desktop pc tower). Playstation will likely follow suit, though to what degree we dont know.

snippet.textDisplay:
I’d like to state my defense of Mark after dark here if you’d let me.

To begin, Marks reaction is more about disproving or correcting things Dunkey says in the video. People say that Dunkey has admitted his flaws about reviewing, that he is impatient and easily bored. This has no bearing on his other complaints, however. Take the terrain discussion for instance: Dunkey didn’t show it, Mark makes a point to explain game mechanics and ways around things Dunkey poses as unavoidable. Mark also discusses how Dunk takes things out of context to make points.


But that’s just my two cents. I had an hour to kill anyway

snippet.textDisplay:
lol, dunky trying to hate on VR, when it's his fault for not having a big brain or has beat the big burrito level yet.


In all seriousness, you don't need to buy the $1000 Index and no VR kit requires an entire room. All VR kits work the same, you can play sitting, standing, or have as much room as you can spare for room-scale. VR requires next to no set-up, especially for inside-out tracked kits like the Rift S. Index and Vive just use lighthouses that you place anywhere in the room and plug them into power. Takes 5 min to setup steamvr too. After you place the lighthouses, there is no need to remove them or place them elsewhere. I haven't touched my lighthouses in over 3 years.
Who gets to play HL:A? Almost over 20 million people that play VR, lol.
HL3 will never happen as long as Gaben is alive, people need to stop asking for it.
